import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y%m%d', errors='ignore')
    ax = sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', label=f'Median: {data["delay"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.boxplot(x='distance', data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    chart.axvline(data['distance'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean distance: {:.2f}'.format(data['distance'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
